SUPER USER DO : 

    RUN COMMAND AS ROOT USER : sudo commands


ROOT : 

    CHANGE USER FROM ROOT : su Username

    CHECK WHO CAN RUN SUDO : sudo cat /etc/sudoers

    EDIT : sudo visudo


/ETC/PASSWD : 

    CHECK USERS : sudo cat /etc/passwd

    EDIT : sudo vipw


/ETC/SHADOW : 

    USER AUTHENTICATION INFO : sudo cat /etc/shadow


/ETC/GROUP : 

    CHECK GROUPS INFO : sudo cat /etc/group

    SEE ALL GROUPS FOR CURRENT USER : groups


USER MANAGEMENT : 

    ADD USER : sudo useradd Username

    ADD USER VIA MORE DETAILS : sudo adduser Username

    REMOVE USER : sudo userdel Username

    CHANGE PASSWORD : passwd Username


   
